Notes on key files
wrangler.toml: Declares bindings (D1, KV, R2, DOs), routes, and dev config. Keep secrets out of git; use .dev.vars for local and Wrangler secrets in the dashboard/CLI for prod.
public/: Pure static assets. You can serve them from a Worker (read from ASSETS using the asset manifest) or use Cloudflare Pages; both work.
migrations/: Use wrangler d1 migrations apply to keep your D1 schema in sync.
src/index.ts: Exports the Worker entry point. Many teams use a tiny router (or a microframework like Hono) to split routes cleanly.
